<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROYCE PEREZ BLACKBURN; OF BLACKBURN TWINS SONG AND DANCE ACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Royce Perez Blackburn, 69, one of the performing Blackburn Twins who appeared 
on stage and television, and in films. Blackburn and his twin brother, Ramon, 
made their Broadway debut at the age of 5 in Jerome Kern's "Music in the 
Air."When they were in the military service during World War II, they appeared 
in the stage and screen versions of "Winged Victory." The song and dance duo, 
who often worked with such stars as Janet Blair and Vivian Blaine, were regular 
guests on the television variety shows of Milton Berle, Steve Allen and Ed 
Sullivan. Among their films were "Take Me Out to the Ballgame" in 1949 and 
"Working Her Way Through College" with Ronald Reagan in 1952. In his later 
years, Royce Blackburn operated a tennis club in New Ipswich, N.H. On April 14 
in New Ipswich of cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
