<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUGH GRAVITT; DRIVER WHOSE CAR KILLED MARGARET MITCHELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hugh Dorsey Gravitt, 74, whose car struck and killed author Margaret 
Mitchell.In August, 1949, the off-duty cabdriver struck Miss Mitchell as she 
walked with her husband, John Marsh, across Peachtree Street in downtown 
Atlanta. Five days later, the 48-year-old author of "Gone With the Wind" died. 
Gravitt was convicted of involuntary manslaughter and served about 10 months in 
prison. In a 1991 interview, he said that Miss Mitchell darted in front of his 
car and that he tried to miss her. In Cumming, Ga., on April 15 of unreported 
causes. 
</P>
