<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEAP FROM FIRE KILLS MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was killed early Sunday after he leaped from a fourth-floor window to 
escape a smoky nursing home fire. Eight people were injured in the blaze, 
including five police officers who helped rescue residents. The cause of the 
fire was under investigation. 
</P>
