<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES HONORS ERICKSON, SIMON AS TOP PLAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nicole Erickson and Miles Simon received the top awards as The Times Orange 
County honored its all-county boys' and girls' basketball first-team members, 
their parents and coaches at an awards breakfast Sunday at the Anaheim 
Marriott. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson, a 5-foot-6 point guard at Brea-Olinda, received the player of the 
year award for the second consecutive year.She has been a starter for the 
Ladycats since her first game as a freshman. Since then, Brea has won 130 games 
and lost five -- a 96% winning percentage. Brea finished 33-0 this season, 
winning its fourth consecutive State championship. Erickson, who averaged 15.7 
points and 8.1 assists, will play next season at Purdue. 
</P>
<P>
 Simon, Mater Dei's 6-4 point guard, was one of the top high school seniors in 
the nation. He led the Monarchs to three Southern Section I-A championships, to 
the Southern California Division I Regional finals three times and the State 
championship game once. Mater Dei finished 33-1 this season, losing only to Los 
Angeles Crenshaw in the Southern California Regional final. Simon, who is also 
player of the year for the second year in a row, will play at Arizona next 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' first team: 
</P>
<P>
 Jessica Eggleston (Cypress), Erickson (Brea-Olinda), Karun Grossman (Dana 
Hills), Colleen Hudson (Brea-Olinda), Michelle Macintyre (San Clemente), Jamie 
Oenning (Woodbridge), Melody Peterson (Mater Dei), Marie Philman (Edison), 
Shandy Robbins (Marina) and Akilah Rodgers (Rancho Alamitos). 
</P>
<P>
 The boys' first team: 
</P>
<P>
 Schea Cotton (Mater Dei), Gil Gonzales (Orange), Doug Gottlieb (Tustin), 
Thomas Harmon (Century), Tim Lin (Los Alamitos), Olujimi Mann (Santa Ana 
Valley), Simon (Mater Dei), Chris Vlasic (Pacifica) and Demitrius Zeigler 
(University). 
</P>
</TEXT>
