<P>
 Boeing Co. Lost 1,187 Workers in Past Month: The Seattle-based company said 
its work force was reduced as it continued to shrink operations to match 
falling demand for its aircraft.Boeing had 111,215 employees as of April 15, 
down from 116,155 at the beginning of the year. Boeing has said it plans to cut 
7,000 jobs this year. The aircraft maker said it laid off 685 workers in the 
month that ended April 15. Another 265 retired and 237 left for other reasons. 
Boeing stock fell 50 cents to close at $43.75 on the New York Stock Exchange in 
afternoon trading Friday. 
