PACIFIC WATCH: TAIWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Industrial Output Increases: Gains in building activity and electronics 
production helped push national industrial production up 5.88% on the year in 
the first quarter, the Ministry of Economic Affairs said.Building activity, 
measured by construction work completed, gained 22.6% on the year in the first 
quarter. Production of electronics and information products increased 11.3% for 
the period. Output of chemicals and metals also increased. 
</P>
