<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: THAILAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Exports Expand Dramatically: Exports during the first two months of this year 
grew 18% from the same period last year due to strong demand from the United 
States, according to a central bank report. Total exports for January and 
February were worth $6.1 billion as industrial exports grew by 20% and 
agricultural exports grew 12%, said Pisit Leeahtham, chief spokesman for the 
Bank of Thailand. Textiles were, as usual, Thailand's largest export, making up 
12% of the total. 
</P>
