<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; COUNCIL TO CONSIDER RAMP REDESIGN PACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura City Council tonight will consider one of the first steps in 
redesigning the Victoria Avenue exit ramp from the Ventura Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 The council will be asked to approve a contract with an Orange County firm to 
refine the state Department of Transportation's preliminary design plans for 
the interchange and recommend the best design for the project. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the city has received $4.5 million in federal funding for revamping 
the interchange, all of those funds must go toward actual construction of the 
ramp. The city itself will pay for the $350,000 design contract and the 
remainder of the estimated project cost of $7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Tom Buford said he was happy to have the money to start on the project. 
"It's exciting to see it go forward," he said. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
