<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS TO TAKE UCI CLASSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ten Tustin High School students have been accepted into UC Irvine's program 
for high school scholars. 
</P>
<P>
 The students, all juniors, will take up to two courses at UCI each quarter in 
addition to their high school classes, said Pete Kellner, a counselor at Tustin 
High School. 
</P>
<P>
 By attending the university program, the students will enter college with some 
of their requirements completed, Kellner said. 
</P>
<P>
 The students are Lakesha Cash, Geoffrey Ching, Kenneth Clark, Krista 
Hollinger, Daniel Hunter-Holly, Eugenia Lai, Noah Margolis, Martin Nakatsu, 
Scott Polston and Eimi Tomimatsu. 
</P>
<P>
 Kellner said the students were selected based on grade-point average, PSAT/SAT 
test scores and recommendations from their counselors. They pay tuition for 
their classes at the same rate as other UCI students, he said. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
