<HEADLINE>
<P>
NONPROFIT GROUPS CAN APPLY FOR FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunday is the deadline for local nonprofit organizations to apply for funding 
from City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 About $8,000 remains to be awarded from the $50,000 the city sets aside each 
year to help charitable groups provide service to the community. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizations do not have to be based in Mission Viejo, but their programs 
must benefit city residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The funding applications are reviewed quarterly and requests are approved 
according to a set of criteria, which includes how many Mission Viejo residents 
use the program and whether the needs the program serves are available to local 
residents elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
 Recipients in recent years have used city funding to help support homes for 
teen-age mothers, services for senior citizens and music outreach programs for 
children. 
</P>
<P>
 The funds can also be awarded to groups organizing special civic events and 
cultural arts programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Groups interested in applying for community service funds can pick up an 
application at City Hall, 26522 La Alameda. For more information, call the 
Community Service Department at (714) 348-2061. 
</P>
</TEXT>
