<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARAFAT AND ZHIRINOVSKY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * We do take exception to the second to last paragraph in an article by Tyler 
Marshall (April 14). In a report from Strasbourg dealing with a speech by PLO 
Chairman Yasser Arafat, he mentions Russian ultranationalist Vladimir V. 
Zhirinovsky was also present at the parliamentary assembly of the Council of 
Europe. 
</P>
<P>
 He writes: "Despite what might appear to be shared anti-Jewish sentiments, the 
two (Arafat and Zhirinovsky) seemed to have little interest in each other." 
</P>
<P>
 This is very misleading. Yasser Arafat is not anti-Jewish. The group of people 
Arafat objects to are the Zionists who have taken Palestinian land by armed 
aggression since 1947. 
</P>
<P>
 Zhirinovsky, on the other hand, is a right-wing Russian reported to have made 
anti-Jewish or anti-Semitic remarks. 
</P>
<P>
 Arafat and Zhirinovsky should not be put in the same category. 
</P>
<P>
 PATRICIA TWAIR 
</P>
<P>
 Regional Coordinator 
</P>
<P>
 National Assn. of Arab Americans 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
