<P>
REGIONAL STUDENT FILMS TO SCREEN AT LOYOLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount University will screen the regional finalists in the Academy 
of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences' 21st Annual Student Academy Awards on May 
6 and 7 at 7 p.m. in the school's Mayer Theater.The screenings are free and 
open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 A jury that includes film editor Jules Engel and Times film critic Peter 
Rainer will judge the films, and the winners will be announced following the 
screening. 
</P>
<P>
 Finalists in the dramatic category will be shown May 6 and animation finalists 
will be shown May 7. There were no experimental finalists selected in the 
region. 
</P>
